{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":560,"text":"Jenni Chang: When I told\nmy parents I was gay,"},{"time":2880,"text":"the first thing they said to me was,"},{"time":5080,"text":"\"We're bringing you back to Taiwan.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":7320,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":10000,"text":"In their minds, my sexual orientation\nwas America's fault."},{"time":13880,"text":"The West had corrupted me\nwith divergent ideas,"},{"time":16840,"text":"and if only my parents\nhad never left Taiwan,"},{"time":19840,"text":"this would not have happened\nto their only daughter."},{"time":23320,"text":"In truth, I wondered if they were right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":26440,"text":"Of course, there are gay people in Asia,"},{"time":28520,"text":"just as there are gay people\nin every part of the world."},{"time":31760,"text":"But is the idea of living an \"out\" life,"},{"time":34720,"text":"in the \"I'm gay, this is my spouse,\nand we're proud of our lives together\""},{"time":38400,"text":"kind of way just a Western idea?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":43160,"text":"If I had grown up in Taiwan,\nor any place outside of the West,"},{"time":46880,"text":"would I have found models\nof happy, thriving LGBT people?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":51960,"text":"Lisa Dazols: I had similar notions."},{"time":53651,"text":"As an HIV social worker in San Francisco,"},{"time":55880,"text":"I had met many gay immigrants."},{"time":57880,"text":"They told me their stories\nof persecution in their home countries,"},{"time":61080,"text":"just for being gay,"},{"time":62600,"text":"and the reasons\nwhy they escaped to the US."},{"time":65080,"text":"I saw how this had beaten them down."},{"time":67240,"text":"After 10 years of doing this kind of work,"},{"time":69280,"text":"I needed better stories for myself."},{"time":71760,"text":"I knew the world was far from perfect,"},{"time":73800,"text":"but surely not every gay story was tragic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":77160,"text":"JC: So as a couple, we both had a need\nto find stories of hope."},{"time":80800,"text":"So we set off on a mission\nto travel the world"},{"time":83760,"text":"and look for the people\nwe finally termed as the \"Supergays.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":87640,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":91760,"text":"These would be the LGBT individuals"},{"time":94240,"text":"who were doing something\nextraordinary in the world."},{"time":97600,"text":"They would be courageous, resilient,"},{"time":99960,"text":"and most of all, proud of who they were."},{"time":102920,"text":"They would be the kind of person\nthat I aspire to be."},{"time":106240,"text":"Our plan was to share their stories\nto the world through film."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110800,"text":"LD: There was just one problem."},{"time":112400,"text":"We had zero reporting\nand zero filmmaking experience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":115480,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":116520,"text":"We didn't even know\nwhere to find the Supergays,"},{"time":118880,"text":"so we just had to trust that we'd\nfigure it all out along the way."},{"time":122000,"text":"So we picked 15 countries\nin Asia, Africa and South America,"},{"time":125440,"text":"countries outside the West\nthat varied in terms of LGBT rights."},{"time":129120,"text":"We bought a camcorder,"},{"time":130400,"text":"ordered a book\non how to make a documentary --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":132567,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":134240,"text":"you can learn a lot these days --"},{"time":136800,"text":"and set off on an around-the-world trip."}]},{"cues":[{"time":140520,"text":"JC: One of the first countries\nthat we traveled to was Nepal."},{"time":144280,"text":"Despite widespread poverty,\na decade-long civil war,"},{"time":147800,"text":"and now recently,\na devastating earthquake,"},{"time":150920,"text":"Nepal has made significant strides\nin the fight for equality."},{"time":154960,"text":"One of the key figures\nin the movement is Bhumika Shrestha."},{"time":160040,"text":"A beautiful, vibrant transgendered woman,"},{"time":163360,"text":"Bhumika has had to overcome\nbeing expelled from school"},{"time":166560,"text":"and getting incarcerated\nbecause of her gender presentation."},{"time":170880,"text":"But, in 2007, Bhumika\nand Nepal's LGBT rights organization"},{"time":176000,"text":"successfully petitioned\nthe Nepali Supreme Court"},{"time":179080,"text":"to protect against LGBT discrimination."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181800,"text":"Here's Bhumika:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":183040,"text":"(Video) BS: What I'm most proud of?"},{"time":184800,"text":"I'm a transgendered person."},{"time":186320,"text":"I'm so proud of my life."},{"time":188120,"text":"On December 21, 2007,"},{"time":191880,"text":"the supreme court gave the decision\nfor the Nepal government"},{"time":195560,"text":"to give transgender identity cards"},{"time":198320,"text":"and same-sex marriage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200280,"text":"LD: I can appreciate\nBhumika's confidence on a daily basis."},{"time":203600,"text":"Something as simple\nas using a public restroom"},{"time":206520,"text":"can be a huge challenge\nwhen you don't fit in"},{"time":209080,"text":"to people's strict gender expectations."},{"time":212160,"text":"Traveling throughout Asia,"},{"time":213880,"text":"I tended to freak out women\nin public restrooms."},{"time":216440,"text":"They weren't used to seeing\nsomeone like me."},{"time":218880,"text":"I had to come up with a strategy,\nso that I could just pee in peace."}]},{"cues":[{"time":222095,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":223400,"text":"So anytime I would enter a restroom,"},{"time":225139,"text":"I would thrust out my chest\nto show my womanly parts,"},{"time":228120,"text":"and try to be as\nnon-threatening as possible."},{"time":230280,"text":"Putting out my hands and saying, \"Hello\","},{"time":232280,"text":"just so that people\ncould hear my feminine voice."},{"time":235680,"text":"This all gets pretty exhausting,\nbut it's just who I am."},{"time":238560,"text":"I can't be anything else."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241480,"text":"JC: After Nepal, we traveled to India."},{"time":244560,"text":"On one hand, India is a Hindu society,"},{"time":248120,"text":"without a tradition of homophobia."},{"time":251040,"text":"On the other hand, it is also a society\nwith a deeply patriarchal system,"},{"time":255320,"text":"which rejects anything\nthat threatens the male-female order."},{"time":259480,"text":"When we spoke to activists,"},{"time":261120,"text":"they told us that empowerment begins\nwith ensuring proper gender equality,"},{"time":266280,"text":"where the women's status\nis established in society."},{"time":269360,"text":"And in that way, the status of LGBT people\ncan be affirmed as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":274440,"text":"LD: There we met Prince Manvendra."},{"time":276920,"text":"He's the world's first openly gay prince."},{"time":280640,"text":"Prince Manvendra came out\non the \"Oprah Winfrey Show,\""},{"time":283200,"text":"very internationally."},{"time":284480,"text":"His parents disowned him"},{"time":285760,"text":"and accused him of bringing\ngreat shame to the royal family."},{"time":289040,"text":"We sat down with Prince Manvendra"},{"time":290680,"text":"and talked to him about why he decided\nto come out so very publicly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":294560,"text":"Here he is:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":295800,"text":"(Video) Prince Manvendra: \nI felt there was a lot of need"},{"time":298360,"text":"to break this stigma and discrimination\nwhich is existing in our society."},{"time":302560,"text":"And that instigated me to come out openly\nand talk about myself."},{"time":307720,"text":"Whether we are gay, we are lesbian,\nwe are transgender, bisexual"},{"time":311200,"text":"or whatever sexual minority we come from,"},{"time":313560,"text":"we have to all unite\nand fight for our rights."},{"time":317640,"text":"Gay rights cannot be won\nin the court rooms,"},{"time":320600,"text":"but in the hearts and the minds\nof the people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":323920,"text":"JC: While getting my hair cut,"},{"time":325680,"text":"the woman cutting my hair asked me,"},{"time":327960,"text":"\"Do you have a husband?\""},{"time":329800,"text":"Now, this was a dreaded question"},{"time":331600,"text":"that I got asked a lot\nby locals while traveling."},{"time":335200,"text":"When I explained to her\nthat I was with a woman instead of a man,"},{"time":338920,"text":"she was incredulous,"},{"time":340280,"text":"and she asked me a lot of questions\nabout my parents' reactions"},{"time":343680,"text":"and whether I was sad\nthat I'd never be able to have children."},{"time":348040,"text":"I told her that there are\nno limitations to my life"},{"time":351080,"text":"and that Lisa and I do plan\nto have a family some day."},{"time":355040,"text":"Now, this woman was ready to write me off"},{"time":357440,"text":"as yet another crazy Westerner."},{"time":360280,"text":"She couldn't imagine\nthat such a phenomenon"},{"time":362320,"text":"could happen in her own country."},{"time":364360,"text":"That is, until I showed her\nthe photos of the Supergays"},{"time":367004,"text":"that we interviewed in India."},{"time":369600,"text":"She recognized Prince Manvendra\nfrom television"},{"time":372040,"text":"and soon I had an audience\nof other hairdressers"},{"time":374303,"text":"interested in meeting me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":375518,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":377400,"text":"And in that ordinary afternoon,"},{"time":379720,"text":"I had the chance to introduce\nan entire beauty salon"},{"time":382680,"text":"to the social changes\nthat were happening in their own country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":387520,"text":"LD: From India,\nwe traveled to East Africa,"},{"time":390160,"text":"a region known for intolerance\ntowards LGBT people."},{"time":394160,"text":"In Kenya, 89 percent of people\nwho come out to their families"},{"time":397680,"text":"are disowned."},{"time":399000,"text":"Homosexual acts are a crime\nand can lead to incarceration."},{"time":402720,"text":"In Kenya, we met\nthe soft-spoken David Kuria."},{"time":406400,"text":"David had a huge mission\nof wanting to work for the poor"},{"time":409360,"text":"and improve his own government."},{"time":411120,"text":"So he decided to run for senate."},{"time":413280,"text":"He became Kenya's first\nopenly gay political candidate."},{"time":417960,"text":"David wanted to run his campaign\nwithout denying the reality of who he was."},{"time":422640,"text":"But we were worried for his safety"},{"time":424320,"text":"because he started\nto receive death threats."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426600,"text":"(Video) David Kuria: \nAt that point, I was really scared"},{"time":429240,"text":"because they were\nactually asking for me to be killed."},{"time":433040,"text":"And, yeah,"},{"time":435880,"text":"there are some people out there who do it"},{"time":438160,"text":"and they feel that they are doing\na religious obligation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":441800,"text":"JC: David wasn't ashamed of who he was."},{"time":444400,"text":"Even in the face of threats,"},{"time":446280,"text":"he stayed authentic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":448880,"text":"LD: At the opposite end\nof the spectrum is Argentina."},{"time":452120,"text":"Argentina's a country where 92 percent\nof the population identifies as Catholic."},{"time":456440,"text":"Yet, Argentina has LGBT laws\nthat are even more progressive"},{"time":460160,"text":"than here in the US."},{"time":462520,"text":"In 2010, Argentina became\nthe first country in Latin America"},{"time":466960,"text":"and the 10th in the world\nto adopt marriage equality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":470440,"text":"There, we met María Rachid."},{"time":472680,"text":"María was a driving force\nbehind that movement."}]},{"cues":[{"time":475320,"text":"María Rachid (Spanish):\nI always say that, in reality,"},{"time":477880,"text":"the effects of marriage equality"},{"time":479480,"text":"are not only for those couples\nthat get married."},{"time":481760,"text":"They are for a lot of people that,\neven though they may never get married,"},{"time":485280,"text":"will be perceived differently\nby their coworkers,"},{"time":487640,"text":"their families and neighbors,"},{"time":490720,"text":"from the national state's\nmessage of equality."},{"time":495200,"text":"I feel very proud of Argentina"},{"time":497080,"text":"because Argentina today\nis a model of equality."},{"time":501120,"text":"And hopefully soon,"},{"time":502720,"text":"the whole world will have the same rights."}]},{"cues":[{"time":507680,"text":"JC: When we made the visit\nto my ancestral lands,"},{"time":510440,"text":"I wish I could have shown\nmy parents what we found there."},{"time":513520,"text":"Because here is who we met:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":515480,"text":"(Video) One, two, three.\nWelcome gays to Shanghai!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":520640,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":526440,"text":"A whole community of young,\nbeautiful Chinese LGBT people."},{"time":532040,"text":"Sure, they had their struggles."},{"time":533560,"text":"But they were fighting it out."},{"time":535840,"text":"In Shanghai, I had the chance\nto speak to a local lesbian group"},{"time":539920,"text":"and tell them our story\nin my broken Mandarin Chinese."},{"time":543600,"text":"In Taipei, each time\nwe got onto the metro,"},{"time":546280,"text":"we saw yet another\nlesbian couple holding hands."},{"time":549480,"text":"And we learned that Asia's\nlargest LGBT pride event"},{"time":553640,"text":"happens just blocks away\nfrom where my grandparents live."},{"time":558040,"text":"If only my parents knew."}]},{"cues":[{"time":561387,"text":"LD: By the time we finished our\nnot-so-straight journey around the world,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":564840,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":566080,"text":"we had traveled 50,000 miles"},{"time":567800,"text":"and logged 120 hours of video footage."},{"time":570480,"text":"We traveled to 15 countries"},{"time":572000,"text":"and interviewed 50 Supergays."},{"time":574080,"text":"Turns out, it wasn't hard\nto find them at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":577480,"text":"JC: Yes, there are still\ntragedies that happen"},{"time":580000,"text":"on the bumpy road to equality."},{"time":582280,"text":"And let's not forget that 75 countries\nstill criminalize homosexuality today."},{"time":587880,"text":"But there are also stories\nof hope and courage"},{"time":591360,"text":"in every corner of the world."},{"time":594600,"text":"What we ultimately took away\nfrom our journey is,"},{"time":597720,"text":"equality is not a Western invention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":602840,"text":"LD: One of the key factors\nin this equality movement is momentum,"},{"time":607160,"text":"momentum as more and more people\nembrace their full selves"},{"time":610560,"text":"and use whatever opportunities they have"},{"time":612720,"text":"to change their part of the world,"},{"time":614960,"text":"and momentum as more and more countries"},{"time":617200,"text":"find models of equality in one another."},{"time":620200,"text":"When Nepal protected\nagainst LGBT discrimination,"},{"time":623760,"text":"India pushed harder."},{"time":625560,"text":"When Argentina embraced marriage equality,"},{"time":628480,"text":"Uruguay and Brazil followed."},{"time":630720,"text":"When Ireland said yes to equality,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":633680,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":637760,"text":"the world stopped to notice."},{"time":639720,"text":"When the US Supreme Court\nmakes a statement to the world"},{"time":642400,"text":"that we can all be proud of."}]},{"cues":[{"time":643760,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":650560,"text":"JC: As we reviewed our footage,"},{"time":652120,"text":"what we realized is that\nwe were watching a love story."},{"time":656080,"text":"It wasn't a love story\nthat was expected of me,"},{"time":658880,"text":"but it is one filled\nwith more freedom, adventure and love"},{"time":663240,"text":"than I could have ever possibly imagined."},{"time":666200,"text":"One year after returning home\nfrom our trip,"},{"time":668760,"text":"marriage equality came to California."},{"time":671760,"text":"And in the end, we believe,\nlove will win out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":678560,"text":"(Video) By the power vested in me,"},{"time":681440,"text":"by the state of California"},{"time":684040,"text":"and by God Almighty,"},{"time":686320,"text":"I now pronounce you spouses for life."},{"time":689680,"text":"You may kiss."}]},{"cues":[{"time":690920,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}